                }
              ],
              "logprobs": [],
              "text": "One recent announcement: Lightricks announced the open-source release of LTX-2 on January 6, 2026. ([rss.globenewswire.com](https://rss.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/01/06/3213304/0/en/Lightricks-Open-Sources-LTX-2-the-First-Production-Ready-Audio-and-Video-Generation-Model-With-Truly-Open-Weights.html))\n\nBrief summary: LTX-2 is a production-ready audio+video foundation model that Lightricks says can generate synchronized audio and video at native 4K (up to 50 fps) for clips up to ~20 seconds, and the company released the model weights, training code, and tooling as an open-source package. ([rss.globenewswire.com](https://rss.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/01/06/3213304/0/en/Lightricks-Open-Sources-LTX-2-the-First-Production-Ready-Audio-and-Video-Generation-Model-With-Truly-Open-Weights.html))",
